article.headline: IUPUI 84, IPFW 57
article.story: FORT WAYNE, Ind. -- Robert Glenn and Gary Patterson each scored 20 points to help IUPUI defeat IPFW 84-57 on Saturday afternoon. Leroy Nobles added 17 points for the Jaguars (10-10, 3-6 Summit). Ben Botts scored 16 points and Zach Plackemeier and Nick Daniels added 10 each for IPFW (8-12, 3-6). IUPUI shot 60 percent from the field and made 10 of 20 3-pointers. Patterson made 6 of 11 threes, while Nobles made 3 of 4. The Jaguars also outrebounded the Mastodons 30-23 and forced 17 turnovers. Glenn led IUPUI with 10 rebounds. IUPUI shot 62 percent in the first 20 minutes to build a 49-25 halftime lead. The Jaguars opened with an 18-3 run and never trailed. IUPUI led by as many as 29 points in the second half. IPFW did not score a field goal in the final 4:32 of the game.
